Sentencas: In this work, (La0.6Sr0.4)0.9Fe0.8Ni0.2O3-5 (LSFN90), a stable, highly ORR-active and cost-efficient perovskite oxide, is developed as cathode materials for solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC).
Titulo: Enhanced oxygen reduction reaction activity and electrochemical performance of A-site deficient (La0.6Sr0.4)1-xFe0.8Ni0.2O3-5 cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The introduction of A-site deficiency results in the crystal expansion of the cubic perovskite phase and an increase in oxygen vacancy concentration at operating temperature.
Titulo: Enhanced oxygen reduction reaction activity and electrochemical performance of A-site deficient (La0.6Sr0.4)1-xFe0.8Ni0.2O3-5 cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The LSFN90 cathode displays good oxygen reduction reaction activity and low polarization resistance values.
Titulo: Enhanced oxygen reduction reaction activity and electrochemical performance of A-site deficient (La0.6Sr0.4)1-xFe0.8Ni0.2O3-5 cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The A-site deficiency facilitates the diffusion of oxygen ions in the electrode and accelerates the surface oxygen exchange reaction.
Titulo: Enhanced oxygen reduction reaction activity and electrochemical performance of A-site deficient (La0.6Sr0.4)1-xFe0.8Ni0.2O3-5 cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: LSFN90 is used as cathode materials for SOFC to prepare anodesupported single cells, achieving maximum power densities of 1.51, 1.27, 0.95 and 0.63 W cm-2 under wet hydrogen (3%H2O-97%H2) atmosphere at 850, 800, 750 and 700 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Enhanced oxygen reduction reaction activity and electrochemical performance of A-site deficient (La0.6Sr0.4)1-xFe0.8Ni0.2O3-5 cathode for solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The introduction of A-site deficiency can greatly enhance the oxygen reduction reaction activity and electrochemical performance of the cathode, demonstrating that LSFN90 has significant potential as a cathode material for practical applications in solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Enhanced oxygen reduction reaction activity and electrochemical performance of A-site deficient (La0.6Sr0.4)1-xFe0.8Ni0.2O3-5 cathode for solid oxide fuel cells
